about.summary: The 'ggdistribute' package is an extension for plotting posterior or other types of unimodal distributions that require overlaying information about a distribution's intervals. It makes use of the 'ggproto' system to extend 'ggplot2', providing additional "geoms", "stats", and "positions." The extensions integrate with existing 'ggplot2' layer elements.

name: r-ggdistribute
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = '1.0.3' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-ggdistribute
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/ggdistribute_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/ggdistribute/ggdistribute_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 5190113097d9281e644b7d844d6dfdde50e3b09fe51d9eef13c54116aeb37a1d

build:
  noarch: generic
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1002
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:

  host:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-tibble
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-data.table
    - r-dplyr
    - r-ggplot2 >=3.0.0
    - r-magrittr
    - r-tibble

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('ggdistribute')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('ggdistribute')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/iamamutt/ggdistribute
  license: GPL-3
  summary: 'The ''ggdistribute'' package is an extension for plotting posterior or other types
    of unimodal distributions that require overlaying information about a distribution''s
    intervals. It makes use of the ''ggproto'' system to extend ''ggplot2'', providing
    additional "geoms", "stats", and "positions." The extensions integrate with existing
    ''ggplot2'' layer elements.'
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - johanneskoester
    - bgruening
    - daler
    - jdblischak
    - cbrueffer
    - dbast
